About
Las Vegas’ hottest new sports and entertainment venue, located just west of the famed Las Vegas Strip, will be officially named T-Mobile Arena. T-Mobile Arena will be the destination in Las Vegas for live events – from amazing music acts to thrilling sporting events – it will set a new standard for what entertainment means in the city that does it best.   • NrthrnGurlEh
    Canada131 contributions
    Easy to get around, nice arena!
    I like the arena. It's small enough to get around easy. They do allow smoking on balconies once you have gotten inside. Read your tickets. When they say "no bags", that also means purses. Purses won't stated on the ticket, I assumed backpacks, gym-type bags, etc. They meant ALL bags bigger than a 8"x3" approx. They do offer lockers, but don't tell you until you have stood in line and ready to go through metal detectors. Be aware. On good note, ebay did offer large clear bags to put your purse contents into. But...it is very expensive to purchase any beverage, somehwat more expense than other places on the Strip. Credit card only, no cash. Seating is generally good anywhere in the arena, depending on the venue. You don't feel swarmed when entering/exiting the arena, like you do at the Sphere. Lot more casual. They provided entertainment outside the arena until the doors opened.
    Visited October 2023
    Traveled with family
    Written November 1, 2023

    GO KNIGHTS GO
    I have seen quite a few hockey games at quite a few arenas. This one is hands down the best arena in North America to watch an NHL game and it’s not contest imo. You can’t beat that vibe and pre show. The interior design is outstanding, and I LOVE that there’s a designated smokers area as the majority of arenas don’t have that. It’s one of the loudest and most energetic buildings I’ve been in and whoever said hockey wouldn’t work in Vegas was clearly wrong. Definitely recommend catching a game during your visit even if you’re not a sports fan, you will have a great time!

    Fun at T-Mobile Stadium
    We went for a hockey game we were amazed. The Vegas Golden Knights played really well but everything else was great to. The VGK theme is medieval Knights and they are all in. It was a show within a show. Before you get in the stadium they have a huge knight mask outside to take pictures with. Once you are inside its welcome to the fortress. They have a huge fortress in the upper stands with a DJ, ice girls and the best seats in the house which they upgrade someone. When a player enters the penalty box everyone chants shame, shame, shame. The players entry onto the ice is a spectacle and so is when the home team scores a goal. The home crowd is all in and it was a very fun hockey game. There was a large food and beverage selection.

Ben
Yuma, AZ54 contributions
Great Venue
Oct 2024 • Friends
We sat in the upper deck, Section 205, and the views were great. The arena is built so that the seating is steep but it puts everyone on top of whatever you're watching. You feel a lot closer than you are. It's very easy to get into and away from. Pretty cool pre/post-game area right outside the arena and easy to navigate your way around inside. The game experience was also awesome; spoke to fans from the visiting team who attend their home games and they said that the atmosphere here was unlike anything they'd experienced at any regular season games they'd ever been to. Lots of fun and the fans are really into it. Had a blast and will definitely be back.
